$ 26Mg values (up to 0.0) reported for chondrites, achondrites, terrestrial basalts and peridotites. To address the issue of inter-laboratory discrepancies on the Mg isotopic composition of silicate rocks, we have prepared 3 pure Mg standards with wide ranging $\delta$ 26Mg (-3.75 to -0.69 with respect to DSM3) as well as a large volume of homogenized olivine from the San Carlos peridotite, which will be available to the scientific community, for future comparative studies. {\textcopyright} 2010 Elsevier B.V.},
